---
title: Coconut Curry with Chickpeas topped with Yogurt & served with Basmati Rice
description: Curries are one of those meals that warm your heart and your belly, and tonight’s vegetarian version is no exception. Chickpeas, onion, and bell pepper get a super savory treatment in a coconut-based curry sauce. Toss that over rice, add a dollop of yogurt and a sprinkle of cilantro, and you have yourself one soul-satisfying meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61b0ce391c26d500b0780fcb-48f2f159.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/coconut-curry-with-chickpeas-61b0ce391c26d500b0780fcb-9f770e51.pdf
cuisine: Indian
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 99 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 18 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 840 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/coconut-curry-with-chickpeas-61b0ce391c26d500b0780fcb
---

Wash and dry produce. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve, peel,
and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1%unit}(finely diced). Core, deseed,
and finely dice @bell pepper{1%unit}(finely diced). Drain and rinse
@chickpeas{13.4%oz can}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}(finely chopped).

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the
garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook until softened and lightly browned,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%oz}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @paprika{1%tsp}, half the
@garam masala{1%tsp}, and remaining garlic until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Love the earthy warmth of garam masala? Add more if you like!

Stir in chickpeas, @coconut milk{5.07%oz can}, @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit},
1/4 cup water, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low;
cook until thickened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: If curry seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls. Top with curry. Dollop with @yogurt{2%tbsp}.
Garnish with cilantro and serve.